column4: <parts.title>[recto] Ad [Addendum] 49. Witt Library. Peasant Wedding Outdoors. Bagpipers on left, Kissing couples on right: 1) Hermsen. Colour repr. with expertises by Hulin & Vogelsang, Canvas, détrempe 35 x 42,3 cm. Verif. Lugt Louvre; 2) Vivant Denon 1829 [sic],  lithograph by Franquinet (?, rechts inverted, schwacher mehr wie P.B.II, wenn das nicht die Technik des Lithographs ist; 3) Photograph Bordeaux. Sky and foliage added at the top; 4) Upright, background on right changed (no kissing couples addition at top and bottom; [verso] 4) continued, Sale Fiévez, Brussels 17-18, V.1923, N° 14 as Pierre Breughel Le Festin, Bois, 48 x 37 cm; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Probably P.B.II'; 5) Adamkiewicz Sale, Glückselig, Vienna 13-14-X-1926, N° 240 Alte Kopie, um 1700, nach Peter Brueghel: Bauertanz. Öl auf Leinwand 75 x 105. Tiny reproduction, much sky added. In this composition there are 4 couples dancing, a fifth is getting ready to dance and a sixth: the woman tries to get the reluctant man to dance.[scan]</parts.title>

<parts.title>Witt Library. Hermsen Composition revised. Bagpipers on right, kissing couples on left: 1) Pure revision, without addition on the sides, only little added at top: Musée Dobrée, Nantes, N° 34, very poor Ph.The following with tree and landscape added on the right: with horizon rather high, Ph. J.R. Hibbard; 2) With sky and foliage added at top; 3) Narbonne Photo; 4) Munich, Photo [...].</parts.title>
